HEADWORD: Subriguous
<hw>Sub*rig"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>subriguus</ets>; <ets>sub</ets> under + <ets>riguus</ets> watered,
akin to <ets>rigare</ets> to water.]</ety> <def>Watered or wet beneath;
well-watered.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Blount.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
